Mexico Stocks: Alfa, Arca Continental, Cemex, Empresas Ica Fall

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-08-18T20:25:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/mexico-stocks-alfa-arca-continental-cemex-empresas-ica-fall.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 2.4 percent to 33,246.63.  Mexican stocks followed U.S. equities lower after Morgan
Stanley cut its forecast for global growth and government data
showed more Americans than forecast filed applications for
 unemployment benefits  last week.  Alfa SAB (ALFAA MM), the world’s largest producer of
aluminum engine heads, retreated 4.7 percent to 150.08 pesos.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, tumbled 6.6 percent to 6.37 pesos.  Empresas ICA SAB (ICA* MM), the country’s biggest
construction company, slid 3.8 percent to 18.25 pesos.  Arca Continental SAB (AC* MM), the Mexican bottling group,
fell 2.9 percent to 58.93 pesos. The company had its
recommendation cut to “hold” from “buy” at Deutsche Bank AG,
which cited the stalling U.S. economy and its impact on northern
Mexico.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
